nts of Bogotá's urban periphery prove a critical site from which to examine the rising effect of security and risk on contemporary cities and urban life.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aEmergency managementxGovernment policyzColombiazBogotá. 0aNatural disasterszColombiazBogotáxPlanning. 0aRisk managementzColombiazBogotá. 0aUrban policyzColombiazBogotá. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374183zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374183423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374183.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles